President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued a memorandum delegating authority to the Secretary of State to direct the drawdown of up to $500 million in defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. This delegation of authority is made under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The Secretary of State is also tasked with making the necessary determinations required under this section to facilitate the drawdown. The memorandum is to be published in the Federal Register.